OL,6,FCladribine is a chemotherapy drug and
OL,7,Fkills certain white blood cells made
OL,8,Fby the immune system known as T and B
OL,9,Fcells.
OL,11,FThese cells normally attack viruses
OL,12,Fand bacteria, but in people with MS,
OL,13,Fthey attack the covering around nerves
OL,14,Fin the brain and spinal cord known as
OL,15,Fthe myelin sheath.
OL,17,FCladribine stops these cells from
OL,18,Fentering the brain or spinal cord and
OL,19,Fattacking the nerves there.
